# Class-R plans (HARD — atom-level)

**Standard:** A plan is wrong until every numeric claim, API name, LOD assert, smoke check, and scope boundary has **file:line or command evidence** from *this* checkout. "Looks right", "should be", "typically", and soft optionals are failures.

Applies to: Plan mode, CreatePlan, finish/audit plans, ticket handoffs, acceptance matrices, Mode A critiques that propose acceptance, any "how we'll know done" table.

Complements: [no-silent-deferrals.mdc](no-silent-deferrals.mdc) (scope), [cursor-agent-workflow.mdc](cursor-agent-workflow.mdc) (who writes code). This rule owns **plan truth**.

Does **not** authorize Cursor to write app code.

---

## Zero-tolerance definition of done (for the *plan*, not the ship)

Before you show the operator a plan, you must be able to answer YES to all:

1. Every constant in the plan was measured in this session (or cited with file:line from code that still matches).
2. Every CDP/smoke assert would **fail** if the feature were absent or stubbed.
3. Every default-camera / default-zoom assert was checked against live LOD gates.
4. Every "out of scope" line is either another ticket ID or a quoted operator deferral.
5. You re-read the ticket summary + cited specs + fold comments and confirmed no named lane/UI/fold was silently dropped.
6. You ran at least one ruthless pass looking for false-green traps (below).

If any item is NO → do not present the plan; measure more.

---

## Mandatory research loop (before CreatePlan)

Run in parallel where possible. Do not draft first and "fill evidence later".

### R1 — Authority (words that define scope)

| Source | Extract |
|--------|---------|
| Operator message | Complete-outcome ask; any explicit "defer/skip X" |
| `.ai/artifacts/*_handoff.md` | Fold locations (file:line), entry points, gate notes |
| `./scripts/ticket brief T-xxx` + registry row | summary, depends_on, unblocks, status, slice_plan parks |
| Cited specs | Draw-order, L-requirements, acceptance tables |
| Fold comments in live code | `fold` / `Deferred` / `later slice` / `follow-on` — these are **must-close** unless operator deferred |

**Ticket shorthand understates specs.** If registry cites `t151_1…t151_5`, the plan includes **all W1–W5 host lanes those specs require**, not only the nouns in the one-line summary ("roads/buildings/trees" ≠ skip sea/contours/landcover/forest mass).

### R2 — Measure every pin (Class R)

For **each** number or enum the plan will assert:

| Kind | How to measure (examples) |
|------|---------------------------|
| Asset bytes | `stat` **and** manifest field — both; must match |
| Census counts | Class-R tests in crates + `ls \| wc` on `packages/` — prefer live over CLAUDE.md |
| LOD constants | Read `lod_gates.rs` / residency aliases — quote exact values |
| Default camera | Read editor mount (`INITIAL_ZOOM`, target, terrain bounds) |
| Engine counters | Read `engine.stats()` format string — **exact snake_case keys** |
| Routes | `app.rs` + handler signature + query struct fields |
| Smoke today | Exact assert expressions + line numbers in `smokes.rs` |
| React parity | `git show <tag>:path` — key **lists and orders** separately |

Put a **Verified constants** table in the plan: `pin | value | evidence`.

No pin → no claim. Soft `> 0` is allowed only when no census exists; if census exists (888 roads, 36 landcover), assert **equality**.

### R3 — LOD / camera visibility matrix (mandatory for any render/UI counter)

If the plan asserts GPU/UI counters at boot:

1. Read default zoom/camera from the host that smokes will open.
2. Build a table: lane → visible at default? → smoke assert.
3. For lanes **hidden** at default, either omit the assert or add an explicit **probe** (set zoom/pan then assert). Never require a counter LOD zeroes.

Known false-green class (map editor @ `INITIAL_ZOOM = -2`):

- Require `tree_glyphs > 0` while `TREE_GLYPH_MIN_ZOOM = 0` → automatic fail/wrong plan
- Require `forest_outline_segments > 0` outside `[FOREST_OUTLINE_MIN_ZOOM, TREE_GLYPH_MIN_ZOOM)` → wrong
- Treat `FOREST_FILL_MAX_ZOOM` as the live fill gate when `class_visible("forestFill")` is `zoom < 0` → wrong

Re-derive from code each time; do not memorize lore.

### R4 — Name and type fidelity

| Wrong (plan smell) | Right |
|--------------------|-------|
| CamelCase invent (`roadSegments`) | Live `engine.stats()` / bridge keys |
| Wasm-only type as Leptos host API (`DemGrid`) | What `map-engine-core` exports (`DemVectorGrid`, …) |
| Stale census (275 chunks) | Live `packages/` + current Class-R test |
| Equating two lanes (`landcover_polygons` == `forest_polygons`) | Separate counters, separate uploads |
| Same keys ⇒ same order (`LOADOUT_ROWS` == `RAIL_REGIONS`) | Lock **both** orders |
| Comment lore (`squads.length === 0`) | Actual smoke check name/expression (`emptyGraph`, …) |

### R5 — False-green catalog (ban these patterns)

A smoke is illegal in the plan if it can pass while the feature is missing:

```text
❌ DOM count on a control type the new UI no longer needs (keep old <select> hidden)
❌ "Stub string gone" without proving live data nodes after the real bootstrap path
❌ "after seed" when seed has no maps/rows and place/hydrate is required
❌ Virtualize only half of a shared list (Editor Layers yes, ORBAT no) when React shared one window
❌ Full-file GET of a 100MB+ LFS asset in CI when the plan claims Range-preview-only
❌ Intercept ≥1 on the wrong endpoint (catalog instead of compat / factions)
❌ Soft presence checks when a Class-R equality pin exists
❌ Claiming tip-React parity while shipping an older fallback (SVG vs 3D) without stating which contract
```

Every CDP row must answer: **what concrete absence makes this assert false?**

### R6 — Scope boundary discipline

**In-scope** = operator ask ∪ ticket summary ∪ cited specs ∪ fold comments ∪ handoff musts.

**Legal out-of-scope** only:

1. Other ticket ID already owning that surface (name it: T-152.5 apron, T-071 Manager, T-154 3D doll, …), **or**
2. Operator-quoted deferral ("defer X" / "skip X") — quote in plan.

Illegal: inventing "skip sea/contours for later", "MVP host wiring without forest mass", "FM pane" when the registry means a full dialog+API, while still claiming the ticket/specs complete.

If unsure whether X is T-166 vs T-152: **read the cited spec's out-of-scope and the other ticket** — then ask the operator only if still ambiguous. Do not guess-skip.

### R7 — Historical ports (React-era framing)

**Historical:** the live SPA is Leptos at `apps/website/frontend/` (T-159 / T-171). When a ticket still requires parity with a deleted React tip:

1. Cite `git show <tag>:<path>` (default tip-of-React tag used by handoff, often `T-159.29.2`).
2. Separate: **behavior contract** (specs + ticket) vs **tip-React extras** (e.g. T-154 remount). State which the ticket locks.
3. Lock ordered key lists independently.
4. Trace data prerequisites (e.g. `ensureDefaultSquad` on place) — a UI tree with empty maps is not done.

