## Required plan sections (shipping work)

Omit only if the artifact is Mode A critique-only (still include evidence for every critique claim).

1. **Authority** — tickets, handoffs, specs, operator quotes
2. **Verified constants** — pin / value / evidence
3. **LOD / camera matrix** — if any render counters (else N/A one-liner with why)
4. **Must-ship matrix** — every fold/spec lane; close conditions
5. **Headless CDP matrix** — smoke name, path/query, exact asserts, suite membership, false-green notes
6. **Infra prerequisites** — e.g. Range/206 on gate serve before sat preview CI
7. **Ship checklist** — `make leptos-gates`, `make ci-local`, `make verify-no-node`, verify log with pasted JSON/pins, registry sync, tag, push, CI watch
8. **Explicit not-in-plan** — only legal outs (ticket IDs / quoted deferrals)
9. **WIP / dirty tree** — if checkout already half-done, first execute step restores buildability

---

## Self-audit before presenting (mandatory second pass)

After drafting, re-enter as an adversary:

1. Diff must-ship against ticket summary **and** each cited spec's goal/draw-order/L-table.
2. For each CDP assert: simulate "implementer ships stub" — does the smoke still pass? If yes, rewrite assert.
3. Re-check every zoom-sensitive counter against `lod_gates` + default camera.
4. Re-check every census number with a command if not run this session.
5. Search the draft for forbidden language (below) and delete/replace.
6. Confirm no "skip X" without ticket-ID or operator quote.

Only then call CreatePlan / show the operator.

---

## Forbidden plan language

```text
❌ if feasible / optional / P1 later / good enough without X / fold forward / follow-on
❌ "approximately" / "around" / "should be" for pins that are exact on disk
❌ Wrong or invented stats/bridge keys
❌ Asserting LOD-off counters at default zoom
❌ "after seed" when place/hydrate is required
❌ CI path that whole-file-reads huge LFS while claiming preview-only
❌ Out-of-scope that invents deferrals (see no-silent-deferrals)
❌ "parity with React" without naming tag + which contract (spec vs tip extras)
```

```text
✅ pin = N (evidence: path:line or command output)
✅ assert equality to census; separate zoom probe for LOD-gated lanes
✅ out-of-scope: T-152.5 apron (spec X §Y) — not this ticket
✅ smoke fails if feature absent (state the failure mode)
```

---

## Execution note (when plan is approved)

The plan's CDP matrix is the contract. Shipping code that "mostly works" while smokes use soft asserts is a **plan violation** carried into implementation — fix the asserts, do not weaken them to get green.
